{
  "changes": [
    {
      "action": "add",
      "createScene": {
        "dialogueGraphs": [
          {
            "id": "DG_SPNDLE_OBSERVE_HOTSPOTS",
            "nodes": [
              {
                "id": "N_EST_01",
                "next": "N_EST_02",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "The observation deck smells like old sealant and fresh paperwork.\nBeyond the window, SPINDLE rotates with the calm indifference of something that never had to justify itself.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_EST_02",
                "next": "N_EST_03",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "Three frames, three tempos, three sets of maintenance markings that do not agree.\nThe central containment sphere is matte\u2014over-insulated, dull, and very much not reflecting anything interesting today.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_EST_03",
                "next": "N_HUB_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "On the deck: a reflectivity test station with a battered readout, a calibration puck in a foam cutout, and a return canister tray with slots labeled in two handwriting styles.\nThe observation window latch has been touched recently. Or someone used a different cleaner. It\u2019s hard to tell.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "choices": [
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_STATION",
                    "next": "N_STATION_01",
                    "text": "look Reflectivity test station"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_PUCK",
                    "next": "N_PUCK_01",
                    "text": "look Calibration puck"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_TRAY",
                    "next": "N_TRAY_01",
                    "text": "look Return canister tray"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_LATCH",
                    "next": "N_LATCH_01",
                    "text": "look Observation window latch"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_WINDOW",
                    "next": "N_WINDOW_01",
                    "text": "look Through the window"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LEAVE_DOWN",
                    "next": "END_LEAVE_DOWN",
                    "text": "leave Control Room - down"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LEAVE_FWD",
                    "next": "END_LEAVE_FORWARD",
                    "text": "leave SPINDLE Chamber Floor (Containment Sphere) - forward"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LEAVE_LEFT",
                    "next": "END_LEAVE_LEFT",
                    "text": "leave Records Hallway and Tube Station - left"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "N_HUB_MENU",
                "speakerId": "PLAYER",
                "type": "player_choice"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_STATION_01",
                "next": "N_STATION_02",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "The reflectivity test station is bolted down like it might run away.\nA laminated procedure card is zip-tied to the frame\u2014updated twice, both updates initialed by someone who didn\u2019t print their name.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_STATION_02",
                "next": "N_STATION_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "The readout is on, not bright. The kind of \u201con\u201d that wants you to stop asking if it\u2019s on.\nA sticky note says: \u201cDO NOT CALL IT MIRROR. \u2014Legal.\u201d",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "choices": [
                  {
                    "id": "C_ASK_WHAT_TESTS",
                    "next": "N_STATION_WHAT_01",
                    "text": "ask What does it test?"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_BACK",
                    "next": "N_HUB_MENU",
                    "text": "look Back"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "N_STATION_MENU",
                "speakerId": "PLAYER",
                "type": "player_choice"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_STATION_WHAT_01",
                "next": "N_STATION_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "The procedure card answers without enthusiasm: \u201cSurface Response Under Controlled Illumination.\u201d\nA handwritten addendum replaces \u201cillumination\u201d with \u201cincident light,\u201d like the old word got someone in trouble.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_PUCK_01",
                "next": "N_PUCK_02",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "The calibration puck sits in foam, immaculate in a way nothing else is.\nIts serial number is stamped twice, as if one stamp wasn\u2019t defensible.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_PUCK_02",
                "next": "N_PUCK_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "A tag reads: \u201cREFERENCE STANDARD \u2014 DO NOT POLISH.\u201d\nSomeone has underlined \u201cPOLISH\u201d hard enough to dent the paper.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "choices": [
                  {
                    "id": "C_USE_PICK_UP",
                    "next": "N_PUCK_PICK_01",
                    "text": "use Pick up calibration puck"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_BACK",
                    "next": "N_HUB_MENU",
                    "text": "look Back"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "N_PUCK_MENU",
                "speakerId": "PLAYER",
                "type": "player_choice"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_PUCK_PICK_01",
                "next": "N_PUCK_PICK_02",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "It has weight, precise and unhelpful.\nThe surface is deliberately boring\u2014engineered to reflect exactly what it\u2019s supposed to, and no more.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_PUCK_PICK_02",
                "next": "N_PUCK_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "Putting it back feels like returning a library book you never wanted on your record.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_TRAY_01",
                "next": "N_TRAY_02",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "The return canister tray is staged under the window line, like it expects traffic.\nSlots are labeled \u201cINBOUND\u201d and \u201cRETURN,\u201d which would be clearer if anything here ever went \u201cbound\u201d in a normal direction.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_TRAY_02",
                "next": "N_TRAY_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "One slot has a printed placard: \u201cEMPTY IS A CONDITION, NOT AN ACTION.\u201d\nIt\u2019s signed with a surname only. No date. That\u2019s deliberate.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "choices": [
                  {
                    "id": "C_ASK_STAGED",
                    "next": "N_TRAY_WHY_01",
                    "text": "ask Why is it staged?"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_BACK",
                    "next": "N_HUB_MENU",
                    "text": "look Back"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "N_TRAY_MENU",
                "speakerId": "PLAYER",
                "type": "player_choice"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_TRAY_WHY_01",
                "next": "N_TRAY_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "A maintenance log clipped to the tray reads: \u201cKeep clear for cycle completion.\u201d\nThe word \u201ccycle\u201d is circled twice, like it tried to escape the sentence.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_LATCH_01",
                "next": "N_LATCH_02",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "The latch is heavy and over-specified: two-step release, interlock indicator, and a little red window that shows either \u201cSAFE\u201d or \u201cNOT SAFE,\u201d with no further nuance.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_LATCH_02",
                "next": "N_LATCH_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "It currently reads \u201cSAFE.\u201d\nSomeone has scratched an asterisk into the metal next to it. No legend. Just the asterisk.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "choices": [
                  {
                    "id": "C_USE_TEST",
                    "next": "N_LATCH_TEST_01",
                    "text": "use Test the latch"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_BACK",
                    "next": "N_HUB_MENU",
                    "text": "look Back"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "N_LATCH_MENU",
                "speakerId": "PLAYER",
                "type": "player_choice"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_LATCH_TEST_01",
                "next": "N_LATCH_TEST_02",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "The handle gives a millimeter\u2014then stops on an interlock that clicks with bureaucratic satisfaction.\nA placard on the frame reads: \u201cDECK OPENING REQUIRES FLOOR PRESENCE CONFIRMATION.\u201d The last two words are in bold, as if they can enforce physics.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_LATCH_TEST_02",
                "next": "N_LATCH_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "You can\u2019t open it from here without making yourself \u201cpresent\u201d in the system, and the system is picky about what counts as you.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_WINDOW_01",
                "next": "N_WINDOW_02",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "The rotating frames stay steady\u2014no wobble, no stutter, no visible heat shimmer.\nThe containment sphere remains matte, swallowing light the way insulation should.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_WINDOW_02",
                "next": "N_WINDOW_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "Below, the reflectivity test station and return canister tray make sense as a pair: test, package, return.\nIt\u2019s the kind of sense that auditors like\u2014simple, repeatable, and wrong in a familiar way.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "choices": [
                  {
                    "id": "C_ASK_NOMINAL",
                    "next": "N_WINDOW_NOM_01",
                    "text": "ask Nominal?"
                  },
                  {
                    "conditions": [
                      {
                        "key": "player.factions",
                        "op": "in",
                        "value": [
                          "OLEA"
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "key": "knowledge.spindleObserved",
                        "op": "!=",
                        "value": true
                      }
                    ],
                    "id": "C_SHOW_MARK_LOG",
                    "next": "N_LOG_01",
                    "text": "show Mark observation in log (OLEA)"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "C_LOOK_BACK",
                    "next": "N_HUB_MENU",
                    "text": "look Back"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "N_WINDOW_MENU",
                "speakerId": "PLAYER",
                "type": "player_choice"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_WINDOW_NOM_01",
                "next": "N_WINDOW_MENU",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "Nominal by visual confirmation: rotation stable, sphere non-reflective, deck instrumentation present and staged.\nIt is not reassurance. It is a checklist item that can survive discovery.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "id": "N_LOG_01",
                "next": "END_NOMINAL",
                "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
                "text": "You record: \u201cSPINDLE observed in nominal state from HUB-12. Containment sphere matte. Reflectivity test station present. Return canister tray staged.\u201d\nYour hands don\u2019t shake, but you catch yourself re-reading the sentence like it might accuse you later.",
                "type": "npc_line"
              },
              {
                "effects": [
                  {
                    "action": "set",
                    "key": "knowledge.spindleObserved",
                    "value": true
                  }
                ],
                "id": "END_NOMINAL",
                "outcomeId": "observe_spindle_nominal",
                "type": "end"
              },
